","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"CD25 como marcador de activación de LB-LT-Macrofago","guid":"XWOQxyHV0RcbTiD1RikskA","children":[]}]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"MO: Hemofagocitosis. (1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"124","text":"LCR: Pleocitosis, hiperproteinorraquia. (1)","guid":"BfY2dhI9czcyGaThSY9Aag","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"124","text":"Genética molecular (HLH 1ria). (1,2)","guid":"W53EvVorUlEGX9C2CLhQlw","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"124","text":"Imagenes","guid":"LLH_qwRttmfEPdeubnw79A","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"Imágenes por resonancia magnética (IRM) o tomografía computarizada (TC) para detectar manifestaciones neurológicas","guid":"53984gt3rxQuRMlMyuy_zQ","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"130","text":"Ecografía o tomografía computarizada para detectar hepatoesplenomegalia","guid":"XWcCXbNpo8y03YJMvLQy5Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"124","text":"Identificar la enfermedad subyacente\\No el desencadenante incluyen","guid":"CpZWGIntKCXsmIoKNHyzMg","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Infección por EBV, familia del virus del herpes como el\\Ncitomegalovirus, el VIH y la hepatitis B y C, y el SARS-CoV-2","guid":"N-S7eoz4WEVT70o83dOslQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"135","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"RaAzphmNdLht2r-JC-q7Fg","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"1° paso","guid":"wQZtXEsEKeNi2v8Uce9kVg","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"Histiocyte Society HLH-2004 criteria\\N≥ 5","guid":"AVX563i_S88Q2Vh24bqyBw","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Fiebre","guid":"rONY197CYSW6MgA1xI-6sg","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"Esplenomegalia ","guid":"MUuV3eTu3liMj3eQQ35Sng","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"137","text":"Citopenia \\N≥ 2","guid":"63h6j1Q9Lrcde8QPqXudPA","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"hemoglobin < 90 g/L (9 g/dL)","guid":"dpBcRYsWqyEB99zBojWSMg","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"platelets < 100 × 109/L","guid":"9iz6Y9_ssghX1E9HYT76GQ","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"140","text":"neutrophils < 1 × 109/L","guid":"zt2wPZ-G1hjf-bh1pL7fVw","children":[]}]},{"id":"144","parent":"137","text":"Hipertrigliceridemia ≥ 265 y/o Hipofibrogenemia ≤ 1.5 g/L [150 mg/dL])","guid":"LfsggLioxYuTb-RMg12ePw","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"137","text":"Hemofágocitosis en médula ósea, linfonodos o bazo","guid":"kqHhnr8uwIiyRwEIN1tqoA","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"137","text":"Actividad de NK baja o ausente","guid":"EiRoRLlZVvMKZNYVsMYabA","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"137","text":"Ferritina ≥ 500 mcg/L (1,123.6 pmol/L)","guid":"N7IoBv3KxUP1Qdtf-TO31w","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"137","text":"Receptor IL2 soluble (sIL-2R) (soluble CD25) ≥ 2,400 units/mL","guid":"OzwNGh2JY40saXm1FVSoRg","children":[]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"136","text":"Score H: Suma variables clínicas/laboratorio. ≥169: 93% probabilidad de HLH. (1)","guid":"Ef53xENWcS0osyxCSducIg","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"136","text":"Otros: Criterios HLH-2009 (HLH/AIJ), EULAR 2016 (HLH/AIJs), MS score 2019 (HLH/AIJs). (2)","guid":"bnA55CHDVzApkXBOdFVN3g","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"135","text":"2° paso","guid":"qeu1OZbphBm4vc81LkmXtA","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"Identificar predisposición o factor desencadenante","guid":"QHmuOlwPEF0z-0zu_LjPLQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"135","text":"3° paso","guid":"MzoDUUd2_atdY4yRPXchBg","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Identificar si es primaria o secundaria","guid":"hjePWSg7nIBPheomQSKQpA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"155","parent":"0","text":"Diagnósticos\\Ndiferenciales","guid":"VkjybDGBTbgBZHd7XD8o4g","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"Sepsis, SIRS, shock séptico. (1)","guid":"Q77A7zN-HFwlzmlMH1yFrA","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"Malignidad hematológica. (1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"Enfermedad autoinmune. (1)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"DalurSwuOgIoFNZDU0miUw","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"1ra línea HLH 2ria: Dexametasona IV\\N+ etopósido ± inmunoglobulina IV. (1)","guid":"Qc_3tHEwStE80g-pB4JNmw","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"Régimen HLH-94","guid":"vYaFjz5R5mOfLpi9aorzWA","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"Inicialmente, dexametasona IV 10 mg/m2/día con o sin dosis modificada de etoposida\\N[150 mg/m2 o 50-100 mg/m2 una vez por semana])","guid":"CcVJw4LHNnzPs50Wqn44rQ","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"161","text":"Con o sin la adición de inmunoglobulina intravenosa\\N(hasta 1,6 g/kg en dosis divididas durante 2-3 días).","guid":"dsWT0tUX2IyfC-df_IiyPQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"164","parent":"160","text":"En el HLH secundario, la continuación de la terapia más allá de las 8 semanas generalmente no es necesaria.","guid":"sZx8e9yViM6-Uwnbwju-qw","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"160","text":"En primario 8 semanas seguidas de la terapia de continuación como puente hacia el HSCT.","guid":"C2Y_-INEZFlQFTb-z4E0cQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"159","text":"Terapias dirigidas: Emapalumab (anti-IFNγ), anakinra (anti-IL1), tocilizumab (anti-IL6). (2)","guid":"VAFqVC85EzYeF9nKKkpcwQ","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"159","text":"Tratamiento de desencadenantes o\\Nafecciones subyacentes","guid":"rVQz8Ctg6YRbystdsBZ1Tg","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Infección ","guid":"nbvbIYRV6U9f4X4B-TFONw","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"Adultos con infección por VEB\\Nu otras infecciones virales","guid":"lkkwjjcbXU8tufvbXcalPg","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"Rápido deterioro clínico","guid":"Yj4Dd3NLeDv2eosUa6nZoA","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Protocolo HLH-94 modificado","guid":"-MPXJdLuodbJqDTjRDmI8A","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"169","text":"La enfermedad no está\\Nprogresando rápidamente","guid":"m-yBDQkdJKMs9Q2yAR8Pqw","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"Considere corticosteroides con o sin inmunoglobulina\\N(IVIG) con etoposida añadida según sea necesario.","guid":"mIYmiHFPeBUvkN3PrcNNCA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"168","text":"Considere rituximab 375 mg/m2 una vez a la semana 2-4 veces para la infección por EBV de células B","guid":"LMMnUkjMULn2mSTcmrBT0Q","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"168","text":"Otros HLH asociados a la infección, como las infecciones intracelulares (tuberculosis, leishmaniasis o enfermedad rickettsial) pueden responder a tratamientos antimicrobianos específicos y pueden no requerir un tratamiento similar a la HLH-94","guid":"5ZAssXHmvz6KvXZ8PT2mBQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"167","text":"Malignidad","guid":"Zm7Z2NuU2VBUqpwVSAdBxw","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"Tratamientos específicos y específicos para tumores","guid":"qbZ64qS1nPDY4KbUguRz3w","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"Corticosteroides para tratar la inflamación (dexametasona 10 mg/m2/día IV). Algunos pacientes pueden requerir dosis más altas de corticosteroides.","guid":"Olw_El2_5rdRzHz9C5iF2A","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"Si la HLH es altamente activa o existe un\\Nriesgo inminente de daño grave a los órganos","guid":"cGTXlWKx_f3be1gNlue7nA","children":[{"id":"180","parent":"179","text":"Considere el uso de etoposide ajustado a la dosis (50-100 mg/m2 una vez por semana) antes del tratamiento específico del tumor.","guid":"XF0I_engkLmGZaCE1h7isA","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"179","text":"El etoposido se puede añadir a los protocolos CHOP (ciclofosfamida, doxorrubicina, vincristina y prednisona) o a los protocolos similares a CHOP.","guid":"u4PBSSbS7YpPvmQkf8lMQw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"182","parent":"167","text":"Autoinmune","guid":"I8TKERm2P522HBZ5Jx4BjQ","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"Dosis alta de corticosteroides (dosis alta de\\Nmetilprednisona de pulso, 1 g/día durante 3-5 días)","guid":"852u5_KnizswrzXakeAz9Q","children":[{"id":"184","parent":"183","text":"± inmunomoduladores. (1)","guid":"O1JSBzI-EyQFp6LoKcKL6w","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"Pronóstico","guid":"YLpg7h98UUUGiYWjJHkh3Q","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"Mortalidad global 20-50% y hasta 70% en algunos subtipos (1,2)","guid":"UvptoSxX7vBD1aeJYKPcTw","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"185","text":"Peor en <2 años, compromiso SNC, citopenias severas, ausencia de trigger, falla tx. (1)","guid":"WIYo8mvqfcwz7X6iHkHXrQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"188","parent":"0","text":"Prevención","guid":"AdoTmBMh3AxL8kDhQ6oLTA","children":[{"id":"189","parent":"188","text":"Diagnóstico molecular precoz en hermanos de pacientes con HLH 1ria. (1)","guid":"BFIm3QjEUIpLLFjnLh-13w","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"188","text":"Trasplante de precursores hematopoyéticos en HLH familiar/recurrente. (1)","guid":"AMAxZFS3P8lp67ylPBKDaw","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":190,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Hematología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Hematología","filename":"Síndrome hematofagocitico-2024-1","id":"map_1093","resolved_references":[]}